      "repair_reason": "- [P2] No automated code repair is identified; the remaining action is maintainer review of the model-choice compatibility effect, CI, and which same-root-cause PR to land.; Cleared: The diff only changes local TypeScript model-id sorting logic and a colocated test, with no dependency, lockfile, CI, secret, publishing, or external code-execution surface changes. (sha=07d54b127712b2fa82d5aa591e01250efd8d7689)",
      "review_summary": "The PR changes both `tryMatchModel` model-candidate sorts to numeric-aware `localeCompare` and adds a `parseModelPattern` regression for double-digit alias version ordering.\n\nPR surface: Source 0, Tests +12. Total +12 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. Source inspection shows `parseModelPattern(\"opus\", [claude-opus-4-9, claude-opus-4-10])` reaches the current plain `aliases.sort(...localeCompare...)` path, and the read-only comparator check confirms the old order picks `4-9` before `4-10`.",
